win31x (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Use categorized high-resolution artwork from the user-supplied Windows 98
    icon archive for the desktop, launcher, minimized clients, and title bars.
  * Make click-to-focus reliably raise clients, including applications with
    their own passive button grabs, and harden focus and transient lifecycle
    handling.
  * Correct desktop-entry escaping, working directories, deep discovery, and
    resize-increment handling; expand real-pointer and provenance tests.
  * Correct bordered-client geometry, window gravity, stack requests, root
    resizing, launcher resizing, and shift-free client withdrawal.
  * Install the supplied session icon through hicolor, enable full hardening,
    and run the Xvfb/XTEST suite during package and QEMU provisioning.
  * Add a desktop Control Panel using the supplied settings, network, display,
    and clock artwork. Configure NetworkManager Wi-Fi, persistent live color
    schemes, and xss-lock/xsecurelock idle locking without exposing passwords
    in process arguments or logs.
  * Extend the XTEST regression suite through the Control Panel and retain
    reliable click-to-focus/raise behavior when its internal window is open.
  * Show visible asterisk feedback for xsecurelock passwords on both idle and
    Lock Now paths, with child-environment regression coverage.
  * Reinstall rebuilt packages during repeat QEMU provisioning even when the
    package version is unchanged.

 -- Win31 X maintainers <maintainers@win31x.invalid>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0800
